<HEADLINE> Chinese Embassy in Manila Celebrates Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese embassy in Manila gave a
reception this evening to celebrate Hong Kong's return to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador Guan Dengming told the reception that
China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong
is "a jubilation for all the Chinese people and also a historical
event of world attention."
</P>
<P>
"China will encourage and support all countries in the world
including the Philippines to further develop and expand exchanges
and cooperation with the Hong Kong SAR (Special Administrative
Region)," Guan said.
</P>
<P>
Among the nearly 600 dignitaries attending the reception were
Philippine Deputy Foreign Secretary Thomas Padivilla and Senate
President Ernesto Maceda.
</P>
<P>
In a speech at the reception, Padivilla expressed his belief
that the friendly relations and cooperation between China and the
Philippines and between the Philippines and the Hong Kong SAR will
be greatly strengthened.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
