<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Scheme to Boost Investment in Innovation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission today
launched a pilot scheme to tackle the insufficiency of private
capital investment in small and medium-sized European enterprises
which are technologically innovative.
</P>
<P>
The scheme, in collaboration with the European Investment
Fund, enters a semi-vacuum where lack of private capital
investment has always been regarded by the EU as a main barrier to
innovation in Europe.
</P>
<P>
The EU notes that small and medium-sized enterprises could
offer the prospect of the technology-led growth Europe needs to
help reduce unemployment and raise competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the program is to encourage venture capital
operators to invest in these enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The scheme was proposed by Edith Cresson, the EU commissioner
responsible for innovation, research and education. It is part of
the First Action Plan for Innovation, adopted by the Commission,
the EU's executive body, at the end of 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
