<HEADLINE> Beijing Welcomes First HK Tourist Group After HK Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The first group of Hong Kong
tourists to travel to the inland areas after the region's historic
homecoming today was warmly welcomed by the National Tourism
Administration (NTA) and the Civil Aviation Administration of
China (CAAC).
</P>
<P>
A large Boeing-747 airliner carrying more than 200 Hong Kong
tourists landed at Beijing's Capital Airport at 11:50 a.m. The
guests received fresh flowers from officials of the head office of
the China International Travel Service under NTA and Air China
under CAAC, and then boarded specially decorated buses sent to
greet them.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming activities were held in front of Beijing Hotel in the
afternoon, featuring lion dances, ethnic dances, and orchestral
music. A team of more than 100 people brandished the national flag
and the regional flag of Hong Kong to greet the guests.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Wendong, deputy director-general of the NTA, gave each
tourist a special photograph album featuring Hong Kong's return at
a reception this evening.
</P>
<P>
"Your arrival will add new color to the national joyous event,"
he said in a speech.
</P>
<P>
The tourists will also watch the national flag-raising
ceremony, visit the rostrum of Tian'anmen, and watch fireworks
displays. A concert will be held for them on July 3. They will
return to Hong Kong on July 4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
