<HEADLINE> Chiluba Advocates Zambia's Own Democracy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick Chiluba said
here today that Zambia should nurture and develop its own democracy
which people will support and embrace as their own but should not be
imposed from the outside.
</P>
<P>
Opening a three-day seminar for parliament members of the country
Chiluba said that his country is still in the process of nurturing and
developing democracy that is compatible with the aspirations of the
Zambian people.
</P>
<P>
"Democracy should not be imposed from outside. We should aim at
sustaining democracy with true roots in Zambia," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said Zambia has achieved spectacular development in the economic,
social and political fields.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba called on the parliament members to use their political
influence freely to transform ideas and policies of the country into
action.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is aimed at orienting the new MPs to parliamentary
practices and procedures to help them debate and contribute
effectively towards the strengthening of democracy. enditem

