<HEADLINE> Song and Dance Drama Celebrates HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A large-sca1ed musical drama
mirroring the historical links between Hong Kong and its
neighbouring province of Guangdong was staged today in the capital
city of Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
An audience of more than 4,000 watched the program with
"Century-long Dream Comes True" as the theme, which tells the
story of the trials and tribulations of people in Guangdong and
Hong Kong in their struggle against imperialism as well as their
present-day close cooperation in economic development.
</P>
<P>
"Blood is thicker than water -- this best describes the
relationship we have to Hong Kong people," said a viewer.
</P>
<P>
Xie Fei, secretary of the Provincial Committee of the CPC, said
in a speech prior to the show that Hong Kong returned to China
only because "China is getting stronger."
</P>
<P>
"I'm fully convinced that people in Guangdong and Hong Kong
will be blessed with a more brilliant future under the guidance of
the reform and opening-up policy and the great theory of 'one
country, two systems'," Xie said.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Hong Kong has become Guangdong's leading
investment source and trading partner, while Guangdong is Hong
Kong's most important base for processing and farm products
supplier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
