<HEADLINE> Reception Held in Malaysia to Mark Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese embassy in
Malaysia gave a reception here this evening to celebrate China's
resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In a speech at the reception, Malaysian parliament speaker Mohd
Zahir said: "We are gathered here this evening to celebrate a
joyful, rare historical event."
</P>
<P>
With the return of Hong Kong to China, he said, "There is an
emerging economy and there is also a developed market."
</P>
<P>
"This is certainly the best form of combination," he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion, Chinese ambassador Qian Jinchang said
history has once again proved that only after the founding of new
China and when China is becoming powerful and her people are
becoming wealthy, can they enjoy the real national pride and can
the family reunion be possible.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of ministers and deputy ministers as well as senior
officials of the Malaysian government were among more than 300
guests who attended the reception.  
</P>
</TEXT>
