<HEADLINE> Gala Gathering in Lhasa to Hail HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Tens of thousands of people gathered
in the Potala Palace Square, the symbol of Lhasa, for
Tibetan-style celebrations of the return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The 1,300-year-old palace was draped with colorful Tibetan
banners printed with words of welcome. 1,997 balloons and 1,997
pigeons were released as the crowd was singing the national anthem.
</P>
<P>
Artists presented a variety of song and dance performances.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few days, Lhasa has been in a festive mood. Red
lanterns and color flags were seen everywhere. Hung over the
streets were banners inscribed with the words "Celebrating the
Return of Hong Kong", "Safeguarding the Unity of the Motherland"
and "Strengthening the National Unity".
</P>
<P>
"History has proved that a unified and prosperous China is in
the best interests of all ethnic groups of the Chinese nation,"
said Gyaincain Norbu, chairman of the Tibet Autonomous Regional
People's Government, at the mass gathering. 
</P>
</TEXT>
