<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Minister Praises Concept of ''One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's Deputy Minister of Foreign
Affairs Nicholas Goche today said Deng Xiaoping's concept of ''one
country, two systems'' paved the way for Hong Kong's return to
China.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''the unique concept of 'one country, two systems', now
being put to test in Hong Kong and due for Macao in two years time,
is no doubt being closely watched world over. We in Zimbabwe wish
the government and people of the People's Republic of China every
success in reintegrating the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
into the mainstream of Chinese life.''
</P>
<P>
He added, ''it is most appreciated that the event we hail
today is the result of peaceful negotiations. We salute the
farsightedness and pragmatism of the Chinese government under the
leadership of Deng Xiaoping, who first mooted the concept of 'one
country, two systems'.''
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at a reception to celebrate Hong Kong's
return to China hosted by Chinese Ambassador to Zimbabwe Liu Guijin.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Liu Guijin said the recovery of Hong Kong is a
major step taken by the Chinese people toward the reunification of
the motherland. It is a victory for the great and unique concept of
''one country, two systems'' devised by late leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
He said it also provides fresh experience in peacefully resolving
international disputes, particularly those left over from history
between nations.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 guests, including Zimbabwean officials, heads of
diplomatic corps in Harare and Chinese experts, attended the
reception. enditem

