<HEADLINE> Reception Held in Indonesia to Mark Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese embassy in Indonesia
tonight held a grand reception here to celebrate the return of
Hong Kong to the motherland today.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,500 people, including Indonesia's Minister of
Social Affairs Endang Kusuma Intan Suweno and Attorney General
Singgih as well as high-ranking military officers, attended the
reception.
</P>
<P>
The participants congratulated China on its resumption of the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong which was under British
colonial rule for more than 150 years.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that the return of Hong Kong to the motherland is
of great significance in the Chinese history and it is also a
historical event of world dimensions.
</P>
<P>
They also spoke highly of the 'one country, two systems'
principle put forward by the late Deng Xiaoping and are confident
that Hong Kong will have a brighter future after its return to
China.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a photo exhibition on the history and development of
Hong Kong was also held here.  
</P>
</TEXT>
