<HEADLINE> Over 20 Palestinians Wounded By Israeli Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 1 (Xinhua) -- More than 20 Palestinian
protesters were wounded by rubber bullets and tear gas during
clashes with Israeli soldiers in Hebron today, according to a
report of JMCC, a Palestinian press service based in East
Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The clashes started when a group of youths broke away from a
procession of several hundred Palestinians, called by political
and religious leadership in Hebron to protest posters pasted on
the Palestinian stores over the weekend depicting Prophet
Mohammed as a pig writing the Koran.
</P>
<P>
Despite condemnations by Israeli leaders of the insulting
poster, the incident is still stirring the feelings of the
Palestinian Moslems. The protesters threw rocks and petrol bombs
at the Israeli troops who responded with rubber bullets and tear
gas. One of the wounded was in serious condition after being hit
by bullets on the head.
</P>
<P>
On the Israeli side, a border policeman was seriously wounded
by an explosive device and another lightly hurt.
</P>
<P>
A general strike will be observed in Hebron Wednesday as
further protest against the posters. The Jewish settlers are
due to hold an emergency meeting tonight to discuss how to
deal with the situation.
</P>
<P>
The city witnessed last month more than 10 days of
violent clashes between the Palestinian residents and Israeli
troops. The Palestinians protested against the U.S. Congress
decision to move the U.S. Embassy from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
