<DOCNO> XIE19970702.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Arrests 15 for Voters Registration Fraud </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The west African peacekeeing force
operating in Liberia known as ECOMOG announced today it has arrested
15 persons involved in voters registration fraud and warned of severe
penalty for offenders.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here quoted an ECOMOG statement as saying "Since
the commencement of the voters registration on June 24, a total of 15
unscrupulous persons have been arrested by ECOMOG for engaging in
various nefarious activities capable of marring the good conduct of
the registration exercise."
</P>
<P>
"Details of the criminal conducts showed that ECOMOG arrested five
persons in different parts of the city for compiling illegal voters
registration in the name of their party, while five others were
arrested for double registration," it said.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, two others were arrested while
attempting to sell their voter's cards to officials of a political
party whose headquarters they went to solicit buyers.
</P>
<P>
The statement said three others were arrested "for either posing as
voters registration officer or intimidating other citizens with threat
of bodily harm at a registration center for not proclaiming a
particular party".
</P>
<P>
It said another culprit, who escaped leaving behind an election
commission registration record book in his bag, is at large.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG, which has vowed to keep security in the west African
country to ensure a free and fair election, said it suspected the
register was "stolen for dubious reasons".
</P>
<P>
Liberia's post-war election is scheduled for July 19 and campaign
of the political parties is in full swing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
