<HEADLINE> Chinese Embassy in Cambodia Celebrates HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Embassy in Cambodia
held a grand reception here today to celebrate Hong Kong's return
to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
President of Cambodia's National Assembly Chea Sim said at the
reception that Hong Kong's return is the result of the the Chinese
government's implementation of appropriate policy, and its long
and painstaking efforts.
</P>
<P>
First Prime Minister Prince Norodom Ranariddh extended
congratulations to China on behalf of himself and Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Cambodia, Yan Tingai, said Hong Kong's
return marked the end of an old era and the start of a new one. He
thanked the Cambodian government and its people for their support
to the resolution of the issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
