<HEADLINE> Australia Faces New Round of Price Cuts on Telephone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The new era in Australia's
telecommunications started today and so did the discount phone
deals.
</P>
<P>
It's Australian communications deregulation day, when the
country's telephone duopoly, namely Telstra Corp and Optus
Communications is blown away and the industry is open to all
comers.
</P>
<P>
The reforms are designed to promote competition and benefit
customers substantially through lower overseas call prices so as
to improve overall economic efficiency by encouraging the
efficient use of, and investment in, telecommunications, according
to an official Industry Commission report.
</P>
<P>
AAP Telecommunications, Australia's third largest
telecommunications company but still relatively unknown outside
the industry, blasted into the public domain with its offer of up
to 55 percent and 60 percent off the costs of national and
international calls, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Telstra Corp today offered a half-price STD happy hour between
5 PM to 6 PM.
</P>
<P>
It's the kind of high profile phone call deals consumers can
expect to see more of, said Richard Alston, Minister for
Communications and the Arts.
</P>
<P>
According to the commission, the country's major
telecommunications companies Telstra and Optus charge five times
what calls cost to provide.
</P>
<P>
The commission said deregulation should force international
call charges down from an average of 1.11 Australian dollars to as
lower as 47 Australian cents.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Australian Communications Authority had its
first meeting today and granted carrier licenses to AAPT, Primus
Telecommunications, Optus and Telstra Multimedia.
</P>
<P>
It said another two licence applications are being considered.
 Australian telephony is dominated by Telstra with about 80
percent of the market. Optus entered the telecommunications market
only six years ago when partial reforms led to Optus entering as
the second legislated carrier.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
