<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Launch Economic Policy Document </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe has now embarked on the second
phase of the economic reform program which will stablise the
macro-economic environment and raise people's standards of living,
President Robert Mugabe said today.
</P>
<P>
The policy document to be launched during the new session of
parliament was expected to further reform the civil service,
parastatals and the financial sector, said Mugabe as he opened the
Third Session of the Fourth Parliament.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''we have now embarked on the second phase of the
economic reform program, the thrust of which is to ensure that the
economy operates efficiently and competitively in order to raise the
standards of living of our people.''
</P>
<P>
''The program is being undertaken in the context of a broader
initiative dubbed Vision 2020,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''in order to implement the vision and realise the
people's aspirations, we are now in the process of formulating the
medium-term plan.''
</P>
<P>
The plan would be used to guide the private sector and the
government ministries in preparing the developmental programs.
