<HEADLINE> Nationwide Activities Mark Hong Kong's Return (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- China was permeated with a festive
atmosphere on the first day after Hong Kong's momentous return to
the motherland, as people throughout the nation celebrated with
pageantry and patriotic fervor.
</P>
<P>
A grand-scale performance and rally attended by more than
80,000 people from various walks of life was held tonight at
Beijing Workers' Stadium. President Jiang Zemin delivered a
40-minute address at the start of the event.
</P>
<P>
After Jiang's speech, 18,000 performers presented the
three-part extravaganza "Celebrate Hong Kong's Return," which
recalled through song and dance China's ascent from national
humiliation to the July 1 Hong Kong homecoming.
</P>
<P>
At the conclusion of the event, a 7,000-square-meter national
flag, formed by people, appeared in the stadium. 1,997-bursts of
fireworks were fired while a narrator recited Jiang's call for
reunification of the motherland and national solidarity.
</P>
<P>
In Shenzhen, the first special economic zone in China and a
neighbor of Hong Kong, people partied throughout last night and at
dawn today welcomed the first group of Hong Kong compatriots to
come "home" over the Lo Wu Bridge in south China's Guangdong
Province.
</P>
<P>
A 40-year-old man surnamed Kwan was the first Hong Kong
resident to cross into Shenzhen, where he was met with crowds of
residents singing and dancing.
</P>
<P>
"I feel so lucky to be the first to come back home," he said.
"I was celebrating the return all night long, and came here
straight afterwards."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
