<HEADLINE> PLA, Armed Police Forces Celebrate Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The People's Liberation Army (PLA)
and the Chinese People's Armed Police Force have joined in the
nationwide celebrations to greet the return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
From midnight Monday till dawn today, offers and men of the
General Departments of the PLA, and the PLA military area
commands of Beijing, Lanzhou, Jinan, Nanjing and Chengdu and armed
police forces watched or listened to the live broadcast of the
ceremony of China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong and viewed a variety of song and dance and other
theatrical performances..
</P>
<P>
They were particularly interested in the entry into Hong Kong
of the armed forces posted there.
</P>
<P>
Many generals and military experts agreed that it would have
been impossible for the army to march into Hong Kong if China had
not grown so strong since the reform and opening up.
</P>
<P>
They expressed the hope that their fellow soldiers stationed in
Hong Kong will strictly observe the Basic Law of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) and the Law Concerning
Stationing Troops to the Hong Kong SAR and perform their duties
with flying colors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
