<HEADLINE> Shanghai People Continue Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- After a sleepless night, Shanghai
citizens today continued their celebrations for the return of Hong
Kong, watching stage shows and fireworks displays and listening to
speeches from officials.
</P>
<P>
Huang Ju, a member of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party Central Committee and secretary of the CPC
Shanghai Municipal Committee, said at a rally this afternoon that
nobody can slow the reunification pace of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the return of Hong Kong will greatly
consolidate the unity of the nation," Huang said.
</P>
<P>
Bao Xinbao, chairman of the Shanghai Federation of Trade
Unions, told the crowd that for Shanghai's workers working hard is
their "historical responsibility."
</P>
<P>
Speaking for non-Communist Parties, Liu Hengchuan said that
more advisory work will be done under the guidance of the CPC to
maintain Hong Kong's prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
On the night of June 30, the economically-prosperous Pudong New
Area was lit up with showers of fireworks. Some 5,000 people
gathered around the Shanghai TV tower, a city landmark, to watch
the displays.
</P>
<P>
Professional actors and actresses staged a 90-minute
performance here to hail the handover. "I wish Hong Kong and
Shanghai will enjoy the same prosperity by developing side by
side," well-known actress Yuan Xuefen recited in a poem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
