<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ties Between Jiangsu, HK Closer After New Airport Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The social and economic contacts
between east China's thriving Jiangsu Province and Hong Kong are
expected to be closer thanks to today's opening of a new airport
in Nanjing, the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
Lukou Airport opened for service today, with a total of 30-plus
flights, including two to Hong Kong, departing or arriving at the
airport.
</P>
<P>
Jointly funded by the Civil Aviation Administration of China
and the Jiangsu provincial and Nanjing governments, the airport,
with state-of-the-art telecommunications, navigation, and air
control equipment, is capable of handling Boeing 747s.
</P>
<P>
Chen Huanyou, secretary of the Jiangsu Provincial Committee of
the Communist Party of China, told Xinhua today that the economic
and cultural exchange between Jiangsu and Hong Kong in recent
years has been more and more frequent.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong has been one of the key trade partners for Jiangsu,"
Chen said. In the past two years, the trade volume between Jiangsu
and Hong Kong exceeded three billion US dollars, accounting for
more than one fourth of the provincial's total.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, some 14,424 enterprises involving funding
from Hong Kong have been registered in the province. The
contractual Hong Kong investment in Jiangsu totaled 18.7 billion
dollars, of which 8.36 billion has been used.
</P>
<P>
"Now that Hong Kong has returned to the motherland, we will
strengthen our cooperation under the prerequisite of mutual
benefit and giving play to each other's advantages," Chen said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
