<HEADLINE> Celebrations Continue in Nanjing To Greet HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- On the first day after Hong Kong's
return to the motherland, the festivities were still going strong
throughout Nanjing, where the ancient Qing Dynasty signed the
Treaty of Nanking 156 years ago which ceded Hong Kong to Britain.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of people gathered for a grand open-air
concert in a downtown square this morning, to welcome Hong Kong's
return.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong is home at last. This washes away the traces of the
156-year humiliation, and every Chinese can't help feeling proud
and elated," said Wang Peiyu, an instructor at a yangko dance
school in Nanjing.
</P>
<P>
Standing behind Wang, were student buglers from a primary
school. "Hong Kong's return has enabled us to realize that only
when our motherland gets strong can it free itself from invasion
and humiliation," said Li Jia.
</P>
<P>
Another large-scale celebration was held in the city this
afternoon to observe the historic homecoming and encourage the
audience to remember China's 156-year period of national
disgrace.  
</P>
</TEXT>
