<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Parliament Endorses Bill for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian parliament, the
House of People's Representatives, today endorsed the proclamation
providing for the establishment of the National Reserve Petroleum
Depot Administration.
</P>
<P>
According to the bill, the importance for the establishment of
the ARPDA arises from the need to set up a legal body responsible
for the construction of national depots and storage of national
petroleum reserve.
</P>
<P>
During the deliberation of the proclamation, participants said
the establishment of the administration is essential to withstand
petroleum shortages that might surface due to natural or man-made
disasters.
</P>
<P>
They said countries like Ethiopia, land-locked and lacking in
petroleum resources, should give due attention to storing
petroleum reserve that at least lasts them from 3-6 months,
adding that Ethiopia presently uses seven depots across the
country with a capacity of 29,900 cubic liters of petroleum which
could cover supplies for only 10 days. enditem

=07011752

=07011801
NNNN
01:55 01:56 g # PAB
</P>
