<HEADLINE> Chongqing Hosts Rally to Mark Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Accompanied by "Ode to the
Motherland," 1,997 pigeons were released to the sky this afternoon,
marking the start of a mass rally in southwest China's Chongqing
Municipality to celebrate Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
Some 3,000 people from all walks of life gathered here to hail
first day of Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Delin, secretary of the Municipal Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), and representatives from different
quarters, made speeches at the rally.
</P>
<P>
"Today is both the 76th anniversary of the founding of the CPC,
and the first day of China's resumption of its sovereignty over
Hong Kong. After 100-year-long vicissitude, Hong Kong has
finally returned to the embrace of the motherland and a
century-long dream of the Chinese people has been materialized,"
Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong, with sufficient capital, advanced technologies and
expertise, will play a more positive role in furthering its
cooperation with Chongqing in the future," he added.
</P>
<P>
Local performers staged colorful shows and a variety of
activities after the rally. 
</P>
