<HEADLINE> Ethiopians Urged to Take Measures to Protect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Children and Youth Affairs
Organization of Ethiopia today urged to take measures to protect
children in the country.
</P>
<P>
The organization's manager Tedla Diresse made the call at a
workshop in Nazreth, 90 kms away from Addis Ababa, said a
report reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Tedla said five million of the Ethiopian children below the
age of 15 are living under appalling conditions.
</P>
<P>
He said tha children lack nutritious food as well as access to
health services and education.
</P>
<P>
Over half a million of the children are orphans, and 2,894
orphans had been taken to 13 European and American countries for
adoption since 1982, he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed: ''Great care should be taken to ensure that the
children not only get access to the basic necessities, but are
also free from fear and worry.'' 
</P>
