<HEADLINE> Armyworm Infestation Put Under Control in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Armyworm infestation occurred
on 1,000 hectares of land in the Harari region, eastern Ethiopia
was put under control, a report said here today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Harari Regional Agricultural Bureau as
saying that the armyworm infestation which hit 454 hectares of
standing crops and grazing land in the areas was put under
control by the joint efforts of development workers and farmers.
</P>
<P>
A total of 277 litres of liquid and 340 kilograms of power
pesticides have been sprayed on 354 hectares of land.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, armyworm which infested East Wollega zone of
Western Ethiopia has been wiped out before causing any damage.
as. But the bureau said that a swarm of woodpeckers is damaging
crops in the same region. 
</P>
