<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Seals Off Illegal Night Clubs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Addis Ababa Regional
Administration has sealed off 123 illegal video houses and night
clubs operating in the city.
</P>
<P>
According to a local press reprot today, Mulatu Nigussie, head
of the cultural department of the administration said that legal
charges would be brought against 123 individuals who had been
engaged in the illegal business of showing video films.
</P>
<P>
He said, as an initial measure failed to curb the ever
mushrooming illicit business in video shows, a special committee
under the regional administration was forced to carry out
successive studies which showed the existence of 180 illegal
video houses in the city.
</P>
<P>
During the raids carried out on the basis of search warrants
issued by courts, 57 of the suspected sites either couldn't be
found or had stopped operation, he added.
</P>
<P>
According to Mulatu, a similar crackdown in November last year
had resulted in the seizure of 42 video decks, 26 tv sets and
many video cassettes. Eleven of the 42 offenders were fined.
</P>
</TEXT>
