<HEADLINE> European Shares Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- All shares on Europe's major stock
markets ended higher today, with London's FTSE-100 index scoring
its biggest one-day gain in point terms for five years.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE-100 of leading British shares closed at 4,728.3, up
123.7 points, catching analysts and dealers by surprise after
weeks of cautious trading.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, shares ended bourse trade at a new closing high
as the export-dependent chemical sector stole the spotlight,
drawing strength from the dollar trading above 1.74 marks.
</P>
<P>
The DAX-30 index closed at 3,819.85, up 34.08 points. In later
screen-based trade the IBIS DAX index ended at 3,834.84, up 67.95
points.
</P>
<P>
Shares on the Paris market extended their gains in afternoon
trade, boosted by Wall Street's early advance on supportive U.S.
data, to set a fresh closing high. The CAC-40 index ended at
2,944.04, up 85.78 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
