<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anti-Malaria Workshop Opens in Yaounde </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A World Health Organization (WHO)
sponsored workshop against malaria opened here today.
</P>
<P>
At the four-day meeting, participants drawn from eight african
countries will review available practical ways of curing malaria
in Africa and developed plans of action on the follow-up of cases
reacting to drugs.
</P>
<P>
The follow-up of cases have been a major strategy adopted by
the WHO.
</P>
<P>
The workshop is organized by the WHO, the Ministry of Public
Health of Cameroon and the Central African Organization for the
Fight Against Endemic Diseases.
</P>
<P>
Malaria is the number one killer disease in African. It is one
of the most important health concerns in more than 90 countries
in the world with an incidence of 300 to 500 million cases each
year. Close to 90 percent of these cases occur in sub-Sahara
Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
