<HEADLINE> Reception in Celebration of Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A grand reception in celebration of
Hong Kong's return to China was held on Tuesday evening at the
Embassy of the People's Republic of China in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the reception, Chinese ambassador Li Fenglin noted
that "the oriental shining pearl" that had been forcibly occupied
by British colonialists for one and a half centuries has at last
returned to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
"The principle of `one country, two systems' is a basic
guideline for our government to run Hong Kong", Li said. "The
Chinese government has solemnly announced to the whole world that
a special administrative region in Hong Kong has been
astablished."
</P>
<P>
More than 700 Russian and foreign guests attended the
reception, including assistant of foreign affairs of Russian
president Sergey Prihoduko, Chairman of the committee of foreign
affairs of State Duma Vladimir Lukin, other leaders of the Russian
State Duma, Russian representatives and friends from all walks of
life and foreign diplomats from various countries.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua news agency Lukin said that China
has given the world a good lecture, and the Chinese people are
lucky to have such a great man as Deng Xiaoping. He solved the
historical problem through the principle of "one country, two
systems".
</P>
<P>
Lukin also expressed his confidence in Chinese leadership who,
he said, is able to maintain the prosperity and steadiness of Hong
Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
