<HEADLINE> Returned Hong Kong To Better Bridge Fujian's Ties With Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Government officials and strategists
here said they believed that Hong Kong would more efficiently
bridge Fujian Province's economic exchanges with Taiwan, though
they preferred them to be done in a direct fashion across the
Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Lin Shouqi, vice-president of the Provincial Statistical
Bureau, said that over 54 percent of the 2.2 billion US dollar
Taiwan capital influx last year into the province along the coasts
of Taiwan Straits came via Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Also, 70 percent of Taiwan's exports to Hong Kong were bought
in China's inland.
</P>
<P>
"Having returned to China, Hong Kong can better facilitate
Taiwan investments' transfer to the mainland," Lin said.
</P>
<P>
Officials said that the mainland and Taiwan should engage in
direct cooperation, and the return of Hong Kong was expected to
boost the trend of establishing these ties.
</P>
<P>
Professor Zhu Tianshun, a Taiwan research specialist with
Xiamen University in Xiamen City, said that the implementation of
the "one country, two systems" policy in Hong Kong will give the
people of Taiwan more faith in the realization of the long-awaited
reunification. 
</P>
</TEXT>
