<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Pledges to Purchase Grain at Protective Price </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji pledged
that the state will buy grain open-endedly at protective prices
after completing the purchase ordered by the state in order to
keep the grain prices on the market stable and protect the
interests of grain growers.
</P>
<P>
The Vice-Premier made the pledge during an inspection tour of
Henan and Anhui provinces in June 25-30.
</P>
<P>
He repeatedly told grain growers in the two provinces that the
state would not lower the purchasing prices of grain and that it
will see to it that grain growing would be profitable.
</P>
<P>
He assured grain growers that the state will purchase the grain
it had ordered at the prices fixed by the State Council last year
and will purchase grain other than that ordered by the state at
the standard price fixed by the State Council, which was 0.69 yuan
per kilogram for wheat in Henan and 0.675 yuan in Anhui. The grain
ordered by the state will be purchased at 0.76 yuan per kilogram
for wheat in Henan and 0.75 yuan per kilogram in Anhui.
</P>
<P>
The Vice-Premier made the pledge following a declining trend in
grain prices on the market after the good harvest of summer grains.
</P>
<P>
He said he was impressed by the summer harvest in central
China, but warned against the declining trend in grain prices,
which, he said, would hurt the grain growers.
</P>
<P>
He urged localities to learn from past lessons and take
immediate steps to stabilize grain prices.
</P>
<P>
He urged the Agricultural Development Bank to provide enough
funds for grain purchase and use well the grain risk fund which
has added up to 15 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
He said greater efforts should be made to increase grain
storage capacity and the state would provide lower-interest loans
in this regard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
