<HEADLINE> PLA, Armed Police Forces Vow to Guarantee Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The People's Liberation Army (PLA)
and the Chinese People's Armed Police Force have vowed to
strengthen the army and guarantee security for the country as it
moves toward reunification and rejuvenation.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the general departments of the PLA have been
reviewing Jiang Zemin's speeches at the handover ceremony in Hong
Kong at midnight June 30 and at a public gathering in Beijing
yesterday to celebrate the return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that Hong Kong's homecoming would not have been
possible without the constant efforts of new China's three
generations of leadership, guided by the Communist Party of China
(CPC) and late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping's great concept of
"one country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
They said Hong Kong's smooth transition gave them greater
confidence in the country's reunification cause.
</P>
<P>
Officials from various PLA military area commands said one of
the most important signs of China's resumption of the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong is the PLA's presence in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
They added that to safeguard the state sovereignty and national
dignity, a country should strengthen its overall national power
and its system of defense. 
