<HEADLINE> Uruguay Beats Ghana in World Youth Soccer Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay defeated Ghana 3-2
after the sudden death extra time in the semifinals of the World
Youth Football Championship at Shah Alam Stadium near here
Wednesday tonight.
</P>
<P>
Both team tied 2-2 after the regular time with Uruguay leading
2-1 at halftime.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay's Marcelo Zalayeta opened the scoring in the 12th
minute. His teammate Walter Coelho Alves added one more in the
44th minute, but Ghana narrowed the gap in the 44th minute through
Odartey Lawson and equalized the score in the 78th minute through
an own goal by Uruguay's Alejandro Melono Botta.
</P>
<P>
In the extra time, Uruguay's Alvaro Perea scored the winning
goal in the 104th minute.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay will meet Argentina in the final on Saturday at the
Shah Alam Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Argentina beat Ireland 1-0 in another semifinals
in Kuching, East Malaysia. 
</P>
