<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Encourages Space Breeding for Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun said
today during a visit to a Beijing-based space breeding center that
space experts and agronomists should increase cooperation in
cultivating fine-quality seeds in a move to promote agriculture in
China.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of the achievements in developing improved
varieties of crops, and encouraged the scientists to expand their
research and spread the use of technology.
</P>
<P>
Space breeding is part of the national seed-development
project, and plays an important role in promoting the rural
economy and environmental protection, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
China began in 1987 to experiment with growing new varieties of
crops in space, using retrievable satellites which took seeds of
more than 400 strains 200-400 km into the sky to see what effects
space had on them. 
</P>
