<HEADLINE> Chinese Arts Exhibitions Open in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Two exhibitions, one featuring
contemporary Chinese block prints and the other featuring
contemporary watercolors, gouache and posters, opened here today
in this north China port city.
</P>
<P>
The 164 pieces exhibited were selected from among 2000
contributed from across the country. Some of them were done by
children. The oldest contributor is 90.
</P>
<P>
A 10-meter-long block print from Southwest China's Sichuan
Province took a record six years to complete.
</P>
<P>
The exhibitions, sponsored by the Chinese Ministry of Culture
and the Tianjin Bureau of Culture, are two of the nine special
exhibitions of Chinese art currently on view. The pieces on
exhibit in Tianjin represent the highest level of works of the
kind in China, experts said. 
