<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds Gala for Return of Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A grand theatrical performance was
held in the Great Hall of the People here tonight as part of the
ongoing nationwide celebrations to hail the return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Among the more than 10,000 audience members were Chinese
President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng, and senior leaders Qiao
Shi, Li Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao and Rong Yiren.
</P>
<P>
The curtain was raised on the stage at the Great Hall of the
People amid the replaying of President Jiang's declaration
yesterday of the establishment of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
"Ode to The Return of Hong Kong" was the theme of the evening,
which is designed to reflect, through songs and dances, the
changes that have taken place in the territory in the past 150
years and to express the nation's joy over the end of a
century-old humiliation, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
The colorfully-decorated stage is on most occasions used for
the chairing of major political meetings.
</P>
<P>
A replica of a Chinese white dolphin, the designated mascot for
the handover event, was hanging overhead, carrying in its mouth a
bauhinia flag -- the emblem of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The gala was co-sponsored by the Ministry of Culture, the
Ministry of Radio, Film and Television, and the General Political
Department of the People's Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
"Recounting the past will help to make the audience aware that
only a strong and prosperous China could make Hong Kong's return
possible," said Tian Junli, chief director of the performances.
</P>
<P>
An ancient poem about homesickness was recited to stir up
patriotic fervor. When young performers held up signs bearing the
words "Love the motherland, love Hong Kong, love mama," the
audience burst into applause.
</P>
<P>
Traditional dragon and lion dances, as well as Beijing Opera,
were other highlights of the evening. Jackie Chan, one of the
guest celebrities from Hong Kong, demonstrated his kungfu skill
and sang along tonight with 2,800 fellow actors and actresses.
</P>
<P>
A moving recitation eulogizing late Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping's historic contributions to accelerating the
reunification with the concept of "One Country, Two Systems"
concept was the high point of the night.
</P>
<P>
"After watching the show, I felt from the bottom of my heart
that the Communist Party is indeed the pillar of our country,"
said a teacher from the Shuncheng Road Primary School. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
