<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Inflation Rate Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia achieved a deflation of
0.17 percent in June this year, bringing inflation rate to 2.54
percent for the first six months from 4.03 percent in the same
period last year, Information Minister Hartono said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after a monthly cabinet meeting on the economy,
Hartono said deflation in June was caused by the 0.73 percent
drop in the food price index.
</P>
<P>
However, the minister said, the price indices of housing,
garment and other materials increased by 0.27 percent, 0.01
percent and 0.09 percent respectively.  
</P>
