<HEADLINE> Vengeance for Killed Vendor May Be Motive Behind </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Vengeance for a killed vendor could
be the motive behind Tuesday's grenade bombing in Pasig City,
Metro Manila, police said today.
</P>
<P>
Chief Inspector Nilo Jambalos, Pasig City police chief, said
his men suspected a group of being responsible for the explosion
that occurred later Tuesday afternoon before a public market.
</P>
<P>
One person was killed and 27 others injured in the incident.
</P>
<P>
Jambalos did not reveal the name of the group, but said the
group could have taken vengeance for the shooting of a vendor in
the same market several days ago.
</P>
<P>
Jambalos did not identify the victim in that alleged shooting.
He added that his men are intensifying a campaign against illegal
vendors in the market.
</P>
<P>
Pasig City Mayor Vicente Eusebio said that the incident had
nothing to do with the celebration today of the 424th anniversary
of Pasig City. 
</P>
