<HEADLINE> Record Investment Agreements Signed To Welcome Hong Kong Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A record number of cooperative
agreements involving 220 million US dollars in total investment
were clinched between Guangzhou and Hong Kong today to celebrate
the homecoming of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The agreements will channel a total of 170 million US dollars
from Hong Kong to Guangzhou, located in southern Guangdong
Province, which will then be distributed to the industrial and
service sectors, and for real estate development and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's return is expected to bring new opportunities to
the foreign trade sector of Guangzhou, and will also be a boon to
the economic cooperations between the two areas," said a local
foreign trade official.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that nearly 81 percent of the overseas
investment in Guangzhou came from Hong Kong, which is also the
entrepot for 80 percent of Guangzhou's exports.
</P>
<P>
The official also said investment in real estate development
has increased, hailing it as a sign for a recovery in the sector
and also as the beginning of a new cycle of economic prosperity
for Guangzhou. 
</P>
</TEXT>
