<HEADLINE> Arafat Visits Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority
President Yasser Arafat arrived here today on a brief visit to
Algeria, it was reported by the Algerian news agency.
</P>
<P>
He was greeted at Algiers airport by Algeria's National
People's Assembly Speaker Abdul Qadir Bin Saleh, Foreign Minister
Ahmed Attaf, and other senior officials.
</P>
<P>
According to well-informed Algerian sources, Arafat will hold
talks with Algerian President Liamine Zeroual on the latest
international developments, regional issues, and the Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
They will examine impediments in the peace process, and the
Judaization policy pursued by Israeli authorities in the occupied
Arab territories, particularly occupied Jerusalem. The two sides
will also discuss the prospects of enhancing bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Algerian observers pointed out that the situation in the Middle
East is quite grave at present as the peace process has reached a
dead end because of Israel's extremist policy.
</P>
<P>
They said Arafat is pinning hopes on the international
community, including the Arab states, to bring pressure to bear on
the Israeli government, and to urge it to abandon its
security-for-peace formula and to accept the land-for-peace
principle instead, and to implement the Oslo peace accord and
related UN Security Council resolutions. 
</P>
