<HEADLINE> Russia's Top Border Guard Happy About Sino-Russia Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Russia's top border guard official
today depicted bright prospects and quick problem solving along
the Russia-China border.
</P>
<P>
General Andrei Ivanovich Nikolayev, the head of Russian Federal
Border Guard Bureau (FBGB), said the development of state
relations between Russia and China will "necessarily" lend
positive influence to the border situation.
</P>
<P>
Nikolayev expressed his satisfaction about the present
situation along the multi-thousand-kilometer border between the
two large countries. He said: "All the problems that occured in
boundary areas can now have a swift settlement through friendly
negotiations."
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the three unprecedented agreements on
mutually defending the border, mutual trust in military affairs
and cuts in border military presence, signed in 1995 between
Russia and China, have yielded good results. Illegal
border-crossings had reduced by five-sixths in the past two years.
</P>
<P>
"It is pleasing," he said.
</P>
<P>
Nikolayev said the task of the FBGB was not to keep Russia
apart from neighboring countries, but to enhance contact with
them. The border guards' main mission was not to battle but to
prevent armed action and crime.  
</P>
</TEXT>
