<HEADLINE> Asian Media Hails Hong Kong's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Major newspapers in Asian countries
hailed Hong Kong's return to China on July 1, calling it a great
historic event in the world.
</P>
<P>
A commentary in India's "Hindustan Times" said Hong Kong's
return to China is a specially significant event because it marks
a real turning point.
</P>
<P>
Another Indian newspaper "National Herald" said Hong Kong's
return indicates the failure of lingering colonialism after the
Cold War.
</P>
<P>
An article titled "Welcoming Hong Kong's Return to China,"
carried in the newspaper "Rodong Sinmun" of the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea, said Hong Kong's return to China was
achieved by the Chinese people through protracted struggle for the
right of self-determination and territorial integrity and the
implementation of the "one country, two systems" policy.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's return was also a great victory for the foreign
policy of the Chinese Communist Party and the Chinese government,
said the article.
</P>
<P>
A commentary in Vietnam's leading newspaper, Nhan Dan (The
People) said that the day of July 1, 1997, would go down in the
Chinese history as a day marking the end of more than 150 years of
foreign colonial rule in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Singapore's leading newspaper "Lian He Zao Bao" said Hong
Kong's return symbolizes not only the end of the 150 year national
humiliation, but also the beginning of a new era of prosperity for
the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
A commentary carried in the Indonesian newspaper "Jakarta Post"
said that after Hong Kong's return, tomorrow's sunshine over Hong
Kong and other Asian areas will be more bright. 
</P>
</TEXT>
