<HEADLINE> Novotna Enters Wimbledon Tennis Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Third-seed Jana Novotna of the Czech
Republic advanced to the semi-finals of the women's singles at the
 Wimbledon tennis championships here on Wednesday when she
defeated Yayuk Basuki of Indonesia 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Novotna, 28, now plays either eighth-seeded Spaniard Arantxa
Sanchez Vicario or Nathalie Tauziat of France for a place in
Saturday's final.
</P>
<P>
The unseeded 26-year-old Basuki, who had reached the
fourth-round four times in her six previous visits, became the
first Indonesian ever to reach the last-eight at a Grand Slam
tournament by defeating Canada's Patricia Hy-Boulais on Tuesday.
