<HEADLINE> Visits to Manila City Jail Suspended After Riot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Visits to the Manila City Jail have
been temporarily suspended from today following a bloody riot that
left three prisoners dead and 35 others injured.
</P>
<P>
The suspension order was issued today by City Jail Warden
Warlito Mosende, who said no visits are allowed because
investigation of the riot is going on.
</P>
<P>
Two gangs in the prison clashed late Tuesday afternoon for
unknown reasons. They exploded a grenade and several home-made
bombs, igniting the fiercest jail riot in Manila in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Mosende said order had been restored inside the jail with the
help of policemen from the nearby Western Police District.
</P>
<P>
Eighteen of the injured had been sent to a hospital while 17
others were treated inside the jail, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
