<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds Gala for the Return of Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A grand theatrical performance was
staged in the Great Hall of the People here tonight to hail the
return of Hong Kong, thus pushing a packed schedule of nationwide
celebrations to yet another high point.
</P>
<P>
Audience members included Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
Premier Li Peng, and senior leaders Qiao Shi, Li Ruihuan, Zhu
Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao and Rong Yiren.
</P>
<P>
The curtain was raised amid the replaying of President Jiang's
declaration on the return of Hong Kong yesterday.
</P>
<P>
"Ode to The Return of Hong Kong" was the theme of the evening,
which involved songs and dances to reflect the changes that have
taken place in the territory in the past 150 years and to express
the nation's joy over the end of a century-old humiliation.
</P>
<P>
The highlight of the show was a specially-written account of
late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping's historic contributions to the
return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,800 performers participated in the pageant, which was
co-sponsored by the Ministry of Culture, the Ministry of Radio,
Film and Television, and the General Political Department of the
People's Liberation Army. 
</P>
</TEXT>
