<HEADLINE> 2 Killed in Lightning Strike in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Two men were killed and nine
others including two women injured when struck by lightning during
heavy rain at the Sabindo beach in Tawau District, Sabah, East
Malaysia, today.
</P>
<P>
The victims, all illegal immigrants from Indonesia, were taking
shelter under a big umbrella while waiting for their boat to
return to Indonesia when the accident happened at about noon, the
Malaysian national news agency Bernama reported, quoting Tawau
police officer Mohamad Haji Ismail.
</P>
<P>
Only one of the victims was identified and the injured were
admitted to the Tawau district hospital, the officer said.
</P>
<P>
The report also quoted an eye-witness as saying he and a group
of people were taking shelter in a stall about 30 meters from the
scene when he saw the umbrella suddenly shattered into pieces.
</P>
<P>
He said he and a few others rushed to the scene and saw the
victims writhing in pain.
</P>
<P>
"Some of them had burnt marks on their legs, hands, head and
body," the eyewitness was quoted as saying.  
</P>
</TEXT>
