<HEADLINE> UN to Help Iran Resist Quake by Satellite </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations will assist
Iranian quake-prone regions with satellite communications
network, Iranian news agency IRNA reported today.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Deputy Interior Minister Rasoul Zargar said that the
international organization will extend a credit of 500,000
U.S. dollars in the form of assistance at the disposal of Iran
for implementing the project.
</P>
<P>
The IRNA report said that the Iranian government and the
U.N. have already signed an agreement on the project which is to
be implemented in phases in the disaster-prone regions of Iran
within a three-month period.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the experience gained and extensive measures taken
by Iran in relief and rescue operations, Zargar said that within
the framework of this agreement and at the request of the U.N.,
educative films on measures taken by Iran will be produced.
</P>
<P>
These films will be at the disposal of other countries to
serve as a model and experience, according to Zargar.
</P>
<P>
Three strong earthquakes have struck Iran since the beginning
of this year.
</P>
<P>
The death toll rose to 2,000 in a 7.1-degree earthquake which
rocked the eastern region of Qa'en and Birjand of Iran on May
10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
