<DOCNO> XIE19970702.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korea's HIV Carriers Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Fifty-six more South Koreans
contracted the HIV virus that causes the deadly disease of
acquired immunodeficiency syndrome (AIDS) in South Korea in the
first half of this year, the Health and Welfare Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The figure brought the total number of HIV carriers in the
country up to 679 by the end of June, the ministry said in a newly
released report.
</P>
<P>
Nine out of every 10 HIV cases were caused by sexual
intercourse, including homosexuality, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
By manner of infection, 238 of the 679 were infected through
heterosexual intercourse in the country, 213 through sexual
contact with opposite sex overseas, 138 through homosexual
activities, 38 through blood transfusions and 28 through other
means. Twenty-three of the 28 those infected through other means
were still undergoing checkups.
</P>
<P>
The number of HIV-positive males was 7.2 times that of their
female counterparts, and 73 percent of infected persons were in
their 20s and 30s, the ministry said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
