<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Economy to Continue Moderate Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 2 (Xinhua) -- German economy will expect a growth of
about two percent this year, falling short of the 2.5 percent
predicted by the Bonn government, an economic research institute
said today.
</P>
<P>
Despite the export boom and a big improvement in trade balance,
Germany will still fail to overcome the weakness in economic
growth and investment both this year and next, said the
Berlin-based German Institute for Economic Research in its latest
economic report.
</P>
<P>
According to its forecast, the economic growth for next year
will remain at two percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the institute also saw no improvement in the job
market, predicting that Germany will still expect double-digit
jobless rates of 11.4 percent this year and 12.1 percent in 1998,
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
