<HEADLINE> Float Parade Celebrates Return of Hong Kong to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A float parade was staged here
this afternoon in celebration of the return of Hong Kong to China
despite an off-and-on subtropical rain.
</P>
<P>
Starting from three o'clock, a fleet of 31 carnival floats
"sailed" through the streets on the northern part of Hong Kong
Island from East Tamar to the Victoria Park.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of spectators huddled under umbrellas along the
streets to watch the two-hour procession.
</P>
<P>
To celebrate Hong Kong's reunion with the motherland is one
purpose of the event, according to the organizer, a
non-governmental body sponsored by the local industrial and
commercial sectors.
</P>
<P>
Another purpose is to extend a message to the rest of the world
that Hong Kong industrial and commercial sectors have full
confidence in the future of Hong Kong.  
</P>
