<HEADLINE> ADB to Act as Economic Maker in SAARC Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
is to play the role of an economic maker in the region of the
South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) to bring
about multilateral economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"We are currently exploring viable projects. Once they are
identified and agreements reached among member nations, ADB will
extend financial assistance," ADB resident representative Shigeko
Asher said here today.
</P>
<P>
The ADB earlier already acted as a match-maker in an
Indo-Bangladesh power exchange project.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC embraces Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives,
Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The ADB will extend financial assistance for techno-economic
studies on the identified projects before providing loans for
their implementation, Asher said.  
</P>
