<DOCNO> XIE19970702.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Halts Military Offensive Against Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- President Fidel Ramos said today
that the military had stopped its offensive against the rebel Moro
Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) as of Tuesday night in Mindanao,
the southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
At his weekly press conference, Ramos said he was informed by
the Armed Forces' Chief of Staff Gen. Arnulfo Acedera that the
military had ceased its offensive against the MILF guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Ramos appealed to the MILF leadership to resume peace talks
with the government to forge a lasting peace, saying he hoped the
halt of the military offensive will help resume the peace process.
</P>
<P>
During the past two weeks, the military carried out an all-out
assault against MILF rebels who were accused by the government of
being involved in many kidnap-for-ransom incidents in central
Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
The military offensive killed more than 100 rebels, soldiers
and civilians and forced more than 65,000 residents to flee their
homes.
</P>
<P>
The offensive, during which a major MILF camp was taken by the
government troops, also prompted the MILF to pull out of the sixth
round of its low-level peace talks with the government scheduled
for the end of June.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
