<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Raises Lending Rate on U.S. Dollar Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
announced today that it has increased the lending rate on its U.S.
dollar loan facility from 6.79 to 6.82 percent per annum.
</P>
<P>
In a press release, the Manila-based bank said the new lending
rate applies to its U.S. dollar loans from July 1 to December 31
this year.
</P>
<P>
The bank said the rate on its multi-currency loans remain
unchanged at 6 percent per annum.
</P>
<P>
The interest rates on the ADB's multi-currency and U.S. dollar
loans are adjusted on January 1 and July 1 each year.
</P>
<P>
For each facility, the lending rate is determined by adding a
spread (currently 0.4 percent per annum) to the preceding six
months' average cost of the respective pools of outstanding bank
borrowings established to fund such loans, according to the
release.  
</P>
</TEXT>
