<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> hkhk-Advisers on Hong Kong Affairs Accomplish Mission (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held here this
morning to mark the end of the term of the advisers on Hong Kong
Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the ceremony, Vice-Premier Qian Qichen said that the
historic contributions made by the advisers to the grand event of
the return of Hong Kong to the motherland "will go down in history
and will always inspire our future generations."
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed the hope that the advisers will continue to
contribute to building the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) in their posts in future.
</P>
<P>
Among those attending the ceremony held in the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center were T.k. Ann Tse-kai, and Henry
Fok Ying Tung, vice chairmen of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, Lu Ping,
director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the State
Council (HKMAOSC), Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive of the HKSAR,
and Zhou Nan, director of Hong Kong Branch of Xinhua News Agency
(HKBXNA).
</P>
<P>
Five years ago, HKMAOSC and HKBXNA decided to jointly invite
representatives of Hong Kong people from all walks of life to be
advisers on Hong Kong affairs, in an effort to do work better
concerning the smooth transition and the handover.
</P>
<P>
The decision was considered a major step to encourage the Hong
Kong people to participate in managing Hong Kong affairs during
the transitional period. Four groups of 186 people served as the
advisers.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's return to China is a historic event for the Chinese
nation, as well as a significant event for the world as a whole,
he said, adding: "All the advisers have contributed to and are
also witnesses to that event."
</P>
<P>
He praised the advisers for the suggestions they had made on
major matters during the late transitional period, the efforts
they had made to publicize the Basic Law, and plenty of
down-to-earth and good work they had done.
</P>
<P>
'"It has proved that advisers on the Hong Kong affairs
constitute an important force of loving the motherland and Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
"With the termination of the transitional period and the
establishment of the HKSAR government, the glorious mission of the
advisers has been successfully accomplished," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the vice premier, it had always been a matter of
great concern to late leader Deng Xiaoping to enable the Hong Kong
people to take part in managing Hong Kong affairs and to create
conditions for "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
"The gradual participation in Hong Kong affairs by Hong Kong
people stressed by Deng Xiaoping also constitutes a guideline for
our work during the transitional period," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the establishment of the Basic Law Drafting
Committee, the Advisory Committee for the Basic Law, the
Preliminary Working Committee of the Preparatory Committee for the
HKSAR and the Preparatory Committee for the HKSAR constituted a
form through which to rely on the Hong Kong people to handle the
Hong Kong affairs and to pave the way for "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong" in a broader sense.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970702.0132 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Advisers on Hong Kong Affairs Accomplish Mission (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A series of activities including consulting activities
organized by the Preliminary Working Committee (PWC) of the
Preparatory Committee (PC) for the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) and the PC, and the application for
the candidates for the Selection Committee were one aspect
involving the participation by the Hong Kong residents. They also
won the support and understanding of Hong Kong affairs advisors,
Qian said.
</P>
<P>
"We are impressed by the unprecedented enthusiasm of the Hong
Kong people about electing candidates for the First Chief
Executive of the HKSAR, as well as the Provisional Legislative
council (PLC)," he said
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the active participation of people from all walks of
life in Hong Kong as masters of their own destiny, preparations
for forming the HKSAR proceeded smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the HKSAR marks the end of the history in
which Hong Kong was ruled by a foreign country and the start of a
new era of "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong", he said.
</P>
<P>
From now on, Hong Kong will be governed by the Hong Kong people
who have become masters of Hong Kong, he said.
</P>
<P>
The HKSAR Government, composed entirely of permanent Hong Kong
residents and comprising the administrative, legislative and
judicial departments, has been set up. Under the leadership of
Tung Chee Hwa, the leading body of the HKSAR Government has made a
very good start in operation, he said.
</P>
<P>
The implementation of "the Hong Kong people governing Hong
Kong" principle requires the involvement and the concerted efforts
of more than six million Hong Kong residents, he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged all advisors to continue to work hard at their posts
and play their roles in future.
</P>
<P>
At present, Qian said, the whole world is observing the
implementation in Hong Kong of the "one country, two systems"
policy, which is an unprecedented great mission.
</P>
<P>
"We will encounter various kinds of problems in implementing
this policy," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Central Government of China is firm and unshakable in its
determination to implement the "one country, two systems" policy.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that with the support of people across
China and the concerted efforts of Hong Kong people, the "one
country, two systems" policy will certainly succeed.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony was presided over by Zhou Nan, director of the
Hong Kong Branch of the Xinhua News Agency.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Qian had a picture taken with all the
advisers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
