<HEADLINE> China's Busiest City Opens Financial Hotlines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 2 (Xinhua) -- China's financial center,
Shanghai, has opened two 24-hour phone lines so the public can
report financial wrongdoings.
</P>
<P>
Calls to (021) 58845022 and (021) 58845064 will be handled by
staff workers during working hours on weekdays and will be
recorded during other periods or on holidays, according to an
official of the Shanghai branch of the People's Bank of China, the
central bank.
</P>
<P>
People can report people who break the law and rules, the
unauthorized establishment of financial institutions,
non-financial organizations engaging in financial affairs, and
other activities violating the financial order, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the phones is to reinforce the supervision of
financial institutions and to improve the financial order, the
official said, noting that the name of the unit or person who
makes the reports will be kept in strict confidence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
