<HEADLINE> Taiyuan Set to Stage Ticket Collecting Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Ticket collectors of a different
sort will be congregating in Taiyuan, capital of north China's
Shanxi Province, on July 18 -- to exchange information and talk
about the sixth most popular form of collecting in China.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 collectors of tourism-related tickets from
different parts of China and from overseas are expected to attend
the fair, believed to be the largest ever held since 1985 when the
first such event was staged.
</P>
<P>
The theme of this year's fair is patriotism and
history. Besides featuring talks, sales, and exchanges, a total of
 50,000 rare tourist tickets will be exhibited.
</P>
<P>
Tourist tickets in China are often large and colorful, and are
kept as souvenirs to places visited by collectors. 
</P>
