<HEADLINE> Thousands of Ugandans Flee to Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of Ugandans have fled
their homes in western Bundibugyo District to eastern Congo as
rebels are terrorizing civilians there, informed sources said
today.
</P>
<P>
World Harvest missionaries based on Uganda-Congo border
estimated the number of the fleeing people between 20,000 and
30,000, but a United Nations' report put the number between 5,000
and 10,000.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Development Program said it will send a
team to assess if further food and other needs are necessary
after 60 tons of maize and other supplies have been sent to
Bundibugyo.
</P>
<P>
Colonel Katumba Wamala, acting commander of the Second
Division of the Ugandan army, said the dispersed rebels of the
Allied Democratic Forces (ADF) are terrorizing civilians.
</P>
<P>
The ADF is a rebel group acting in western Uganda. It sent 250
rebels in mid-June to Bundibugyo and tried in vain to isolate the
district from the other parts of Uganda and use it as a
bargaining chip against the government, Colonel Katumba noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
