<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Monument in Shenzhen Marks Return of Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A monument in marble and bronze
bearing reliefs depicting the cession and return of Hong Kong was
unveiled here Tuesday to mark the return of Hong Kong to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
The upper part of the monument, carved out of white marble and
in shape of a sail, is 19.97 meter high, while its 4-meter-high
foundation is cast in bronze and engraved with historical reliefs.
</P>
<P>
The idea of erecting the monument, which stands 23.97 meters in
height on Luohu Bridge linking Shenzhen and Hong Kong, was
proposed by the Guangdong Branch of Xinhua News Agency and funded
by Dr. David S.H. Chu of Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
