<HEADLINE> Return of Hong Kong Marked in Los Angeles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Consulate General
in Los Angeles, the United States, held a reception here today to
celebrate China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Hong Kong is a significant step toward peaceful
reunification of our motherland," said the Chinese Consul General
Feng Shusen.
</P>
<P>
Addressing 1,500 guests at present, Feng said that the idea of
"one country, two systems," which shows its vitality in the case
of Hong Kong, has been supported by the Chinese people and
acclaimed worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Among the guests were local citizens of Chinese origin as well
as native Americans. Officials from the city of Los Angeles, Los
Angeles county, Orange county, the city of Long Beach, presented
plates of congratulations.
</P>
<P>
They wished Hong Kong to be more prosperous in the future and
voiced the hope to strengthen economic and trade ties between
California and Hong Kong and other areas of China. 
</P>
