<HEADLINE> Bridge Collapse Kills 4 People in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The collapse of the Taghiabad
bridge on the Qarchak Varamin route, southern Tehran, left four
dead and five injured Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that as a result of
this incident several spans of the bridge collapsed. A pick-up
truck and an automobile traveling on the route were buried in the
rubble.
</P>
<P>
However, the reasons for the collapse of the bridge has not yet
been determined, according to an official of the fire brigade of
the city.
</P>
<P>
Three relief and rescue teams from the fire brigade rushed
to the scene of the accident as soon as it happened and
operations to clear the rubble continued until after midnight.
</P>
<P>
A local official said that the bridge had been constructed by
a contractor and a consultant engineer in the private sector and
the responsibility for its collapse lies primarily with them.
</P>
<P>
He said the collapse could be attributed to the excavation work
and laying the foundation of the linking roads.
</P>
<P>
The municipality has lodged a court complaint against the
consultant engineer and the contractor, the official added.
</P>
</TEXT>
