<HEADLINE> Thailand, HKSAR Ink 30-day Visa-Free Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A new agreement on the 30-day
exemption of visa for Thai and Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (HKSAR) passport holders takes effect today.
</P>
<P>
The pact was signed by Thai Foreign Minister Prachuab
Chaiyasarn and HKSAR Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa this morning in
Hong Kong, Thai Foreign Ministry sources said.
</P>
<P>
It is the first agreement signed between Thailand and HKSAR
after Hong Kong's return to China on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Senior Thai Foreign Ministry officials also noted that the
signing of the agreement marks the Thai government's confidence in
the future of Hong Kong and it will help promote tourism, trade
and economic cooperation between Thailand and HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
Previously, Thais only have 14 days of visa-free access to Hong
Kong, while Hong Kong people visiting Thailand are allowed for
stay without visa up to 30 days.  
</P>
