<HEADLINE> Chinese Embassy in Turkmenistan Celebrates HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Embassy in
Turkmenistan today hosted a grand reception to celebrate the
return of Hong Kong to the motherland after 156 years of British
colonial rule.
</P>
<P>
More than 130 people, including officials and other dignitaries
from various circles of Turkmenistan, foreign diplomats and
representatives of international organizations, attended the
reception.
</P>
<P>
Turkmenistan's Assembly Speaker Sakhat Muladov, Deputy Prime
Minister and Foreign Minister Boris Skikhmuradov were also present
at the reception.
</P>
<P>
Skikhmuradov conveyed Turkmen President Saparmurad Niyazov's
congratulations on Hong Kong's return to China, and said that
China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong
was a major event in the world.
</P>
<P>
The deputy prime minister also said that the concept of "one
country, two systems," initiated by the late Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping, provided a new way to settle international disputes.
</P>
<P>
He said he hoped that Sino-Turkmen relations would further
develop after the return of Hong kong to China.
</P>
<P>
He added that Hong Kong should serve not only as a bridge of
Sino-British friendly relations, but also as a bridge of
friendship between China and the rest of the world. 
</P>
