<HEADLINE> Gift to HK from Central Government Attracts Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The giant sculpture
"ever-blooming Bauhinia", a gift from the Central Government to
the newly established Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR), has become a hot tourist attraction.
</P>
<P>
Though the area leading to the sculpture located at the
waterfront of the HK Convention and Exhibition Center by the
Victoria Harbor was blocked Tuesday for celebrations for the
inauguration of the HKSAR, local residents and foreign tourists
were seen busy viewing and taking pictures of the art work on
balconies and corridors at nearby buildings.
</P>
<P>
The sculpture featuring bauhinia, the regional flower of HKSAR,
was erected yesterday as a central government gift for the HKSAR,
which was inaugurated in the small hours of July 1.
</P>
<P>
Measuring six meters high, 6.6 meters long and wide, the
sculpture is made of bronze and coasted with gold foils. It has a
cylinder-shaped base
</P>
<P>
The glittering bauhinia represents profound feelings and best
wishes of the Central Government for the HKSAR, a viewer said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the gift from the Central Government, 31 provinces,
autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central
Government in China's interior areas also presented gifts to the
HKSAR to honor HK's return to the motherland.  
</P>
