<HEADLINE> More Beer Brewed in Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
produced 284,200 tons of beer during the January-April period, up
19.7 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Brewers in the province, which faces Taiwan across the Taiwan
Straits, are now producing different brew to meet market needs,
offering both low-alcohol and low-sugar content beers to consumers.
</P>
<P>
During the January-May period, the coastal province sold 35,376
tons of beer, a rise of 17 percent on 1996 sales during the same
period.
</P>
<P>
Fujian brewers produced 1.06 million tons of beer last year,
3.41 times that for 1991, and 8.3 percent up on 1995 output.
Brewing and sales hit a peak during the hot summer months. 
</P>
