<HEADLINE> Twelve HK Residents Receive SAR Medals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Twelve Hong Kong permanent
residents today received the Grand Bauhinia Medal (GBM), the top
honor of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The medal is issued to honor the recipients' long-time
fostering among Hong Kong people the love for the motherland,
their concern about and support for China's accomplishments and
outstanding contribution to the Hong Kong community.
</P>
<P>
HKSAR Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa presented the medals in the
presence of Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen.
</P>
<P>
Recipient K.L. Wong is a member of the Standing Committee of
the Chinese People's Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National
Committee. He is a banker of high standing who has made invaluable
contributions to the banking and securities sectors of the
mainland and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Recipient Ann Tse Kai is Vice Chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC). He is a leader in Hong Kong's textile industry
and has a keen interest in cultural studies.
</P>
<P>
Recipient Cha Chi Ming is a member of the Preparatory Committee
for the HKSAR and a Hong Kong Affairs Adviser. He is concerned
about the welfare of the Hong Kong community. He is also a
prominent figure in the textile industry of Hong Kong and has made
invaluable contributions to promoting the development of science
and technology in China.
</P>
<P>
Recipient Chung Sze Yuen is a member of the Preparatory
Committee for the HKSAR and a Hong Kong Affairs Adviser. He is a
distinguished member of his profession and also dedicates much of
his time to public service.
</P>
<P>
Recipient Simon F.S. Li is vice chairman of the Preparatory
Committee for the HKSAR and a Hong Kong Affairs Adviser. He
dedicates himself to public service.
</P>
<P>
Recipient Tsang Hin Chi is a member of the Standing Committee
of the NPC. He has made invaluable contributions to the promotion
of trade between the mainland and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Recipient S.P. Chuang is a Standing Committee member of the
CPPCC National Committee. He has made invaluable contributions to
the banking industry of Hong Kong. He concerns himself with the
well-being of the community.
</P>
<P>
Recipient Elsie Tu is a Hong Kong Affairs Adviser to China, a
member of the Selection Committee of the first government of the
HKSAR and member of the Provisional Legislative Council of the
SAR. She has stood up for the interests of grassroots members of
the Hong Kong community for several decades.
</P>
<P>
Recipient Xu Simin is a Standing Committee Member of the CPPCC
National Committee, a representative of overseas Chinese in the
National People's Congress (NPC). He is engaged in the cultural
sector and is a commentator on politics. He is also a patriotic
overseas Chinese who is committed to promoting China.
</P>
<P>
Recipient Q.W. Lee is a Hong Kong Affairs Adviser and a noted
member of the banking industry in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Recipient Fok Ying Tung is Vice Chairman of the CPPCC National
Committee and a representative of the NPC. He has contributed
greatly to the well-being of the community and the promotion of
sports in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Recipient T.S. Lo is a member of the Preparatory Committee for
the HKSAR and a Hong Kong Affairs Adviser. He is an experienced
lawyer who is committed to public service and has served on
various important public bodies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
