<HEADLINE> China To Participate in Quadrilateral Talks on Korean Peninsula </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- China has agreed to take part in
quadrilateral talks on the Korean Peninsula issue, according to
Tang Guoqiang, a Foreign Ministry spokesman who says that China
stands for building a peace mechanism for the Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
Tang said today that the idea of maintaining peace and
stability on the peninsula has always guided China's handling of
matters related to it. And from this position, Tang said, "We
agree to the establishment of a peace mechanism for the Peninsula
and have adopted a positive attitude towards the quadrilateral
talks."
</P>
<P>
China welcomes the agreement reached by parties concerned on
holding preliminary talks, he added, noting that China, as a
signatory to the Korean Armistice Agreement and one of the
countries next to the Peninsula, agrees to take part in the talks.
</P>
<P>
China will also continue to cooperate with the parties
concerned and will play a constructive role in the process of
establishing a peace mechanism for the Peninsula, the spokesman
said.  
</P>
