gift to the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), has
drawn a lot of spectators.
</P>
<P>
Although the area leading to the site of the sculpture located
at waterfront of the HK Convention and Exhibition Center was
blocked Tuesday for inauguration activities for the Hong Kong SAR,
local residents came to appreciate the work of art and posing for
pictures with it from balconies and corridors in adjacent
buildings.
</P>
<P>
The sculpture featuring bauhinia, the regional flower of Hong
Kong SAR, was erected yesterday by the Victoria Harbor at the new
extension of the Exhibition and Convention Center.
It was a valuable gift presented by the Central People's
Government to the Hong Kong SAR government on its inaugural day,
July 1.
</P>
<P>
Measuring six meters high, 6.6 meters long and wide, the
sculpture is made of bronze and coasted with gold foils. It has a
cylinder-shaped base with a square bottom.
</P>
<P>
The glittering bauhinia represents profound feelings and best
wishes of the Central Government for HKSAR, a viewer said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the gift from the Central Government, 31 provinces,
autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central
Government in the interior areas also presented their gifts to the
Hong Kong SAR to honor it return to the motherland. 
