During the period under review, prices in Serbia were stable
with a monthly price rise not exceeding 1 percent, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the currency, Dinar, has also been kept stable, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Marjanovich attributed the economic achievements primarily to
measures that have been taken by the government to stabilize the
economy and stimulate production and export. 
