<HEADLINE> Three More Ranking Officials Flee Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Three more ranking officials have
fled Albania over the past two days, local radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The officials, who belong to the Democratic Party, left the
country after the Socialist Party won the parliamentary elections
on June 29.
</P>
<P>
They were Belul Cela, minister of the Interior of the All-party
Interim Government of Albania, Agim Shehu, vice minister of the
Interior and director of the Police Office, and Xhahid Xhaferri,
commander of the National Guard.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Bashkim Fino has decided to appoint Lush
Perpoli, state secretary of the Ministry of the Interior, as the
acting minister.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sokol Baraj, who has no party affiliation, was
appointed as vice minister of the interior and director of the
Police Office. Dashamir Sheli, who is in charge of defense affairs
for the president, was appointed as commander of the National
Guard.
</P>
<P>
Since a riot took place in Albania in March, many ranking
officials, such as former defense minister Safet Zhulali and
former director of the National Intelligence Bureau Bashkim
Gazidede, have fled the country. 
</P>
