<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Chief Executive Presents Medals of Honor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), today
presented the Grand Bauhinia Medal GBM) in the HKSAR Government's
honors system to 12 recipients at Government House.
</P>
<P>
The recipients are Ann Tse Kai, Elsie Tu, Simon F.S.Li, Q.W.
Lee, Cha Chi Ming, Xu Simin, K.L. Wong, Tsang Hin Chi, S.P.
Chuang, Fok Ying Tung, Chung Sze Yuen and T.S. Lo.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen attended
today's ceremony. Over 100 local dignitaries were also present.
</P>
<P>
The Chief Executive's Office said the Grand Bauhinia Medal is
the highest award in the honors system. The recipients must be
Hong Kong permanent residents who have displayed distinguishing
merits over a considerable period.
</P>
<P>
It requires that those so honored have, for a long time,
fostered among Hong Kong people a love for the motherland; showed
concern about and support for, and also identified with, China's
accomplishments; and made an outstanding contribution to the Hong
Kong community.
</P>
<P>
The honors list will be announced annually on July 1.
</P>
</TEXT>
