<HEADLINE> Nepali Newspaper Hails HK Return as Historic Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- China's resumption of the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong from July 1 is a historic
handover, and there is every reason to expect Hong Kong to forge
ahead in the days to come, the Rising Nepal newspaper said today.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali national newspaper said in an editorial that the
Basic Law guarantees the Hong Kong people a high degree of
autonomy and they are now the masters of their own destiny.
</P>
<P>
The editorial said that considering the Hong Kong people's
vitality, dynamism, business acumen and entrepreneurship -- which
helped transform Hong Kong to one of the world's financial centers
-- there is every reason to expect Hong Kong, as a Special
Administrative Region of China, to forge ahead in the days to
come.
</P>
<P>
The editorial noted that the handover sounded the death knell
of the last remnants of foreign rule in China, or almost, since
China still has two years left to exercise its sovereignty over
Macao.  
</P>
</TEXT>
