<HEADLINE> Venezuela, Paraguay to Enhance Bilateral Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan President Rafael Caldera
said here today that his country hoped to strengthen friendly and
cooperative relations with Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at a meeting with Paraguayan Foreign
Minister Ruben Melgarejo, who is on a 2-day visit here to pave the
way for the official tour of Paraguayan President Juan Carlos
Wasmosy on July 28-30.
</P>
<P>
Melgarejo and his Venezuelan counterpart Miguel Angel Burelli
outlined a framework for promoting bilateral ties, a statement
said at the end of Ruben's visit on July 1.
</P>
<P>
They agreed to send trade missions to each other's country and
establish joint companies to strengthen and complement different
aspects of their economies.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers highlighted the importance of
regional cooperation as the world's economy becomes more
globalized. They agreed that the Rio Group, the bloc formed by 14
Latin American countries to promote regional integration, is the
best forum for dialogue and negotiation for its member countries.
</P>
<P>
They also promised to strengthen cultural and diplomatic ties
and work together in the fight against drug trafficking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
