<HEADLINE> Brazilian Media Hail HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian media lauded
Hong Kong's return to China today as "opening a new era" for Hong
Kong after more than 150 years under British colonial rule.
</P>
<P>
Today's major newspapers devoted pages to the coverage of the
handover ceremony and various celebrations across China, saying
China has healed the wound of more than a century of national
humiliation and embarked on a new age of national unity.
</P>
<P>
One newspaper carried an editorial entitled "Hong Kong Begins
New Era", which said the Chinese people, with 5,000 years of
civilization, "are filled with national pride" after the reunion
with Hong Kong, ending the history of suffering from foreign
bullying.
</P>
<P>
Other dailies, including O Estado de Sao Paulo, Jornal do
Commercio and Jornal do Brasil, carried photographs and detailed
background stories of the historical event, hailing the day as "a
triumphant day for China."
</P>
<P>
The newspaper O Globo on Monday carried an editorial, saying
China has wiped out its long-standng national shame by embracing
Communism. "It is the Chinese Communist Party that has fulfilled
the dream of clearing national shame," the article said. 
</P>
