<HEADLINE> Chile Hopes HK's Return to China Will Open up Better Era </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chilean Foreign Minister Jose
Miguel Insulza said today the return of Hong Kong to China "marks
the end of a whole era and we hope it will open up a better one."
</P>
<P>
Insulza had been invited to Hong Kong's handover ceremony
midnight Monday. He told the newspaper La Tercera that Hong Kong's
return to China showed "very good omens" and described the
ceremony as "very beautiful, well constructed and very dignified."
</P>
<P>
As for the presence of the Chinese military in Hong Kong, the
foreign minister said that "there was no increase in soldiers,
rather a visible decrease, to one-half. The Hong Kong police were
absolutely in charge of everything."
</P>
<P>
He said, "the truth is that I do not see a difficult
situation. Quite the contrary, the situation is very calm (in Hong
Kong)," an area occupied by Britain for 156 years.
</P>
<P>
Insulza also expressed confidence that trade between his
country and China will increase considerably. 
