<HEADLINE> Thai Car Parts Exports up 133 Percent in 5 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's exports of cars,
motorcycles, engines, parts and accessories in the first five
months of this year were valued at 8.23 billion baht (317 million
US dollars), a jump of 133.5 percent from the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
Car exports alone in the period soared by 646 percent to 11,740
units, worth 3.75 billion baht (144 million US dollars), said
Surapong Phaisitpatthanapong, spokesman for the Federation of Thai
Industries' Automobile Industry Club.
</P>
<P>
However, car assembly in January-May totalled 215,645 units, a
drop of 5.47 percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Passenger cars alone totalled 69,450 units, accounting for
32.21 percent of total car assembly.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the assembly of family type of motorcycles in the
period dropped by 7.67 percent and sports models fell by 40.85
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
