<HEADLINE> Myanmar Paper Urges EU Not to Follow U.S. Sanctions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar official paper The New Light
of Myanmar today urged the European Union (EU) and Canada not to
follow the United States in its sanctions against the country.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. government announced economic sanctions against
Myanmar on May 20, banning further the U.S. investment in the
country because of its human rights and democracy situation.
</P>
<P>
The paper blamed the U.S. of ignoring positive things which are
happening in Myanmar presently, saying that infrastructural
development is taking place at a phenomenal pace with little or no
external support.
</P>
<P>
The paper cited the surrender of the 15 major insurgent groups,
who have been up in arms against successive governments for half a
century, saying that they have chosen a peaceful settlement at a
time when a military government is in power.  
