<HEADLINE> Colombia's Coffee Production Falls Short of Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's coffee
production fell by 23 percent in the last nine months, unlikely to
meet this year's production target of 10.2 million sacks (60
kilograms per sack).
</P>
<P>
The National Federation of Coffee Growers said on Monday that
late rain was the main cause of the drop in coffee production.
</P>
<P>
Production between October 1996 and June 1997 was 8.2 million
sacks while the official estimate for the next three months was
only 1.5 million sacks.
</P>
<P>
Columbia's coffee sales in the last nine months totaled 10
million sacks, of which 8.8 million sacks went abroad and 1.2
million sacks were consumed at home. 
</P>
