<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Cocaine Seized in Argentina This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's police say
seizures of cocaine have soared this year. Some 700 kilograms of
the drug were confiscated in the first six months of this year,
against 900 kilograms for the whole of 1996, police said today.
</P>
<P>
Over the past six months, police have carried out 20
anti-narcotics operations in different parts of the country,
arresting 31 dealers and seizing 700 kilograms of marijuana and
26,000 kilograms of coca leaves in addition to the 700 kilos of
cocaine.
</P>
<P>
Drugs enter Argentina mainly through its northern borders with
Bolivia and Paraguay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
