<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Foreign Minister Congratulates HK's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Minister of State and
Foreign Minister Adrian Severin today congratulated China on Hong
Kong's return to the motherland, saying that it is an event of
great significance.
</P>
<P>
Severin expressed optimism over the future of Hong Kong. "We
are not worried at all about the future of Hong Kong," he said at
a reception held by Chinese Ambassador Liu Guchang at the Chinese
Embassy to mark the occasion.
</P>
<P>
China today resumed the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong,
which had been under British colonial rule for more than one and a
half centuries.
</P>
<P>
Severin said his country will continue its friendly relations
with China. Whether or not Romania could join NATO, whatever may
happen in the world, ties with China will remain one of the top
priorities of Romania's foreign policy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Constitutional Court President Ioan Muraru, who was also
present at the reception, said the return of Hong Kong completely
conforms to the principles of international law.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's return sets an unprecedented example for peaceful
solution of disputes, he said.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the reception were Interior Minister Gavril
Dejeu, Supreme Court President Gheorghe Uglean, chief presidential
advisor Petre Zoe, former president Ion Iliescu, other government
officials, and leaders of political parties and social dignitaries.
</P>
<P>
Some 700 people attended the reception. 
</P>
</TEXT>
