<HEADLINE> Thailand's Half-year Inflation at 4.4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's inflation for the first
six months of this year was down to 4.4 percent, compared to 6.8
percent in the first half of 1996, according to a senior Business
Economics Department official.
</P>
<P>
Karun Kittisataporn, director-general of the department,
credited the drop on the government policies aimed at combating
inflation and an ample supply of agricultural goods on the market
this year.
</P>
<P>
Inflation in June rose 4.4 percent over the same month last
year, but was up only 0.2 percent from May, according to Karun.
</P>
