<HEADLINE> Chinese Seminar on Energy Consumption and Environmental Impact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Experts and scholars from Europe and
China gathered in the capital of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region on Monday for a three-day seminar on energy
consumption and its impact on the environment.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, there were 23 academic papers
presented. Participants are expected to discuss how mankind will
use existing energy resources more effectively and develop new
pollution-free energy resources to protect the environment.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang is one of China's most important energy bases. For a
decade or more major energy infrastructure projects have been
built there, and the power industry has become a major force
there, said Wang Huaiyu, vice chairman of the regional government.
</P>
<P>
He said that the seminar could advance Xinjiang's research in
energy development and environment-friendly science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was organized by the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region and the European Commission Directorate General 12.
</P>
