<DOCNO> XIE19970702.0243 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Records Big Strides in Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong's foreign trade strode
forward forcefully in the first five months of this year, today's
China Daily quoted the provincial customs office as saying.
</P>
<P>
Total imports and exports soared 20.3 percent from a year ago
to be worth about 46.8 billion US dollars with exports rocketing
up 32.2 percent to approach 27 billion US dollars and imports
edging up 7.2 percent to reach 19.8 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The report said that exports through general trade witnessed
rapid growth and imports through general trade saw a slight
increase.
</P>
<P>
Total exports through general trade more than doubled the
amount one year earlier to record 6.8 billion US dollars while
imports through general trade rose 5.9 percent to approximate 2.1
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Imports and exports through processing trade grew steadily with
total trade value surpassing 34 billion US dollars, up 16 percent,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Value of exports through processing trade exceeded 19.6 billion
US dollars, up 16.6 percent. And imports were 14.4 billion US
dollars, up 15.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, State-run enterprises, reversing the
year-long trend, outpaced foreign-funded enterprises in both
imports and exports in the January-May period.
</P>
<P>
State-run enterprises scored total imports and exports worth
more than 20 billion US dollars, growing at a rate of 27.8
percent, while foreign-related enterprises chalked up about 25
billion US dollars, increasing at a rate of 15.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Light textile products dominated the exports and raw materials
and badly needed goods dominated the imports, the report pointed
out.
</P>
<P>
Exports of textiles and garments ranked first with the total
amount valued at about 3.9 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Other goods that came under the top 10 exports include: shoes
worth more than 1.7 billion US dollars, toys 1.12 billion US
dollars, plastic products 890 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, preliminarily shaped plastics topped the top
10 imports with the total amount worth 1.9 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
What followed were steel materials valued at 1.15 billion US
dollars, integrated circuit and microelectronic components valued
at 850 million US dollars, paper and paper board valued at 670
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
A majority of the exports went to Hong Kong, the United States
and the European Union, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
