<HEADLINE> Tung Signs First Hong Kong SAR Agreement With Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chief Executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), Tung Chee Hwa, and
Foreign Minister of Thailand Prachuab Chaiyasarn signed a
vise-free agreement here this morning.
</P>
<P>
This is the first agreement signed since Tung was sworn as the
HKSAR chief executive in the small hours of July 1.
</P>
<P>
The document is on mutual exemption of visa requirement for
holders of HKSAR passports to visit Thailand and Thai passport
holders to visit for Hong Kong for 30 days.
</P>
<P>
Tung said at the signing ceremony: "The signing of the
agreement reflects the Thai government's confidence in the 'one
country, two systems' concept and Hong Kong's continued stability
and prosperity."
</P>
<P>
The Chief Executive added that he had no doubt that the other
countries would follow suit in joining the increasing list of
countries or territories granting HKSAR passport holders visa-free
treatment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
