<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Beats Spain at European Basketball Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia outplayed the host Spain
79-70 in the second round of the European Basketball Championship
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Both teams have booked berth in the quarterfinals of the
tournament.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia's center Zeljko Rebraca opened up space in the
middle, scoring 16 points while guard Nikola Loncar added 17
points on shots from above the Spanish zone.
</P>
<P>
Spain narrowed the lead to 68-65 with four minutes remaining on
the inside play of center Alfonso Reyes, who scored a total of 20
points, and the slashing drives of forward Mike Smith, 14 points.
</P>
<P>
However, Yugoslavian forward Dejan Bodiraga's three-point
basket with two minutes remaining in the contest put an end to
Spain's last attempt to steal the contest.
</P>
<P>
In Tuesday's other games, Turkey beat France 82-71, Greece
downed Israel 85-82, Poland defeated Germany 86-76. 
</P>
