<HEADLINE> Shanghai-Hong Kong Joint-Venture Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The first joint-venture financial
institution of Shanghai and Hong Kong has been set up in
Shanghai's Pudong New Area.
</P>
<P>
First Sino Bank was founded by the Shanghai Pudong Development
Bank and Lotus World Wide Limited with a combined capital of 100
million US dollars, the largest of all overseas-funded financial
institutions registered in Pudong.
</P>
<P>
First Sino will provide financial services for overseas-funded
enterprises. It will also support major infrastructure projects,
help attract more overseas funds for major projects in Pudong, and
promote economic, trade, and financial cooperation between
Shanghai and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Financial experts say that Hong Kong has become an important
source of financial cooperation between Shanghai and the rest of
the world and that the new bank will help boost the city's effort
to become an international financial center. 
</P>
