<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East Chinese Cities Becoming larger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Statistics Bureau of Fujian
Province in east China said that cities in the province grew
during the 1987-1996 period.
</P>
<P>
A study of population, land area, revenues, and retail spending
of the people of Fujian showed that the number of cities went from
11 in 1987 to 23 in 1996 and the urban population from 4.68
million to 13.46 million.
</P>
<P>
The area of cities went from 15,000 square kilometers in 1987
to 40,440 square kilometers in 1996 and their revenues, from 1.9
billion yuan in 1987 to 14.5 billion yuan in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Retail spending of urban residents went from 5.5 billion yuan
in 1987 to 57.7 billion yuan in 1996, and accounted for 70.7
percent of the province's total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
