MANAGUA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Nicaraguan President Arnoldo Aleman
announced today that he will pay a state visit to Mexico next
September 18 and 19.
</P>
<P>
"It will be an official visit at the invitation of Mexican
President Ernesto Zedillo," said Aleman at a working breakfast
with the foreign press accredited in Managua.
</P>
<P>
According to the Nicaraguan president an agenda for his visit
is being prepared and a Mexican delegation will arrive this month
to discuss Nicargua's debt with Mexico and the signing of a free
trade agreement with other countries also participating.
</P>
<P>
Aleman pointed out that Nicargua wants a scheme that "will
allow our sugar to be exported to Mexico."
</P>
<P>
As for the possibility of the signig of an agreement during his
visit to Mexico, the president of Nicaragua said that it is still
too early to talk about that.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that Mexico, together with the United States, is
"Central America's big brother".
</P>
<P>
He added that the recent parliamentary approval of the tax bill
in Nicaragua, which becomes effective today, has opened the door
to the signing of a free trade agreement with Mexico.
</P>
<P>
"The passage of the bill opens our economy to that country,"
said the president of Nicaragua. 
</P>
</TEXT>
