<HEADLINE> Safety on China's Guangzhou-Kowloon Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Guangzhou-Kowloon railway
line, which links the capital of south China's Guangdong Province
with Kowloon in Hong Kong has carried more than 30 million
passengers in the 18 years since it reopened in April of 1979.
</P>
<P>
The 178-kilometer line was built in 1911, but ceased operation
in 1949. In the 18 years since it resumed operation, more than 150
engineers have safely handled 46,000 trains and the railway has
safely covered 8.2 million kilometers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
