<HEADLINE> Romania Lauds HK's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian Foreign Ministry
today hailed China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty
over Hong Kong, saying it is a positive example of solving
territorial disputes through peaceful negotiations at the
international arena.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in a statement that the policy of "one
country, two systems" would ensure the long-term prosperity in the
Special Administrative Region of Hong Kong and maintain the
metropolis' status as an international economic, trade and
financial center.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that achieving the island's reunification
with China through peaceful means contributed to the maintenance
of peace and stability in southeast Asia. 
</P>
