<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Mixed Before Fed's Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street were mixed
Tuesday, with blue-chip shares rising as new data reinforced hopes
the Federal Reserve won't see a need to raise interest rates this
week or in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 49.54 to 7,722.33, after
giving back a 75-point morning gain and rebounding in the late
session.
</P>
<P>
Reports released on the day suggested some moderation in
factory activity and construction spending, giving a boost to the
bond market first.
</P>
<P>
Now few observers expect this week's Fed meeting to produce any
change in the central bank's key lending rates.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 3-to-2 margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume was heavy at 539.41 million
shares down slightly from Monday's busy pace.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 5.89 to 891.03, the
NYSE composite index rose 3.57 to 466.01, and the American Stock
Exchange composite index rose 3.04 to 625.61.
</P>
<P>
But the Nasdaq composite index, which is dominated by
technology shares and smaller companies, fell 3.82 to 1,438.25,
and the Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 2.24 to
394.13.




