<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Photo Exhibition on Hong Kong's Return Opens in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A week-long photo exhibition opened
here today at the Athens exhibition center to mark China's
resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July
1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the Chinese Embassy in Greece, the exhibition
features some 80 pictures that fully displayed Hong Kong's
history, the process of transfer of power and today's Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Addressing at the opening ceremony, Mr. Fotis Papathanassiou,
representative of mayor of Athens, said that they were very glad
to be present at the special photo exhibition to celebrate with
the Chinese people the return of Hong Kong to China after it had
been ruled by Britain for more than 150 years.
</P>
<P>
He wished an ever brighter future for both Hong Kong and China.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Greece Yang Guangsheng said at the
ceremony that the Chinese government are more confident about the
sustained prosperity and stability of Hong Kong, and capable of
making the region's future even better.
</P>
<P>
About 400 people, including Greek government officials, foreign
diplomats and overseas Chinese attended the exhibition tonight.
</P>
</TEXT>
